<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="147" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to Mr.
                                        <persName type="to">Conger</persName>, through
                                    Consul-General at Shanghai.</hi></head>
                            <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-14"><hi rend="italic">August 14,
                                        1900</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                            <p>(Mr. Adee states that armistice has been asked by Chinese Government,
                                through Li Hung Chang, to which reply has been made that Mr. Conger
                                must first be delivered to relief column at Pekin. The relief column
                                captured Ho-si-wu on August 8, and is supposed now to be near
                                Tung-Chow. Courage.)</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>